# Skillet Public API (Third-Party Contract)

`ThirdPartyHooks.lua` documents methods whose **names and behavior must not break**. Treat this file as a compatibility boundary.

## Do Not Change Without Strong Justification

- Method names/signatures on `Skillet` listed in `ThirdPartyHooks.lua`
- Return shapes documented in the TradeSkill Query API (`Recipe`, `Reagent`, `Profession`, `Character`)
- Hook-chain semantics: chained methods must call prior hook results and combine (concatenate text, take max width, etc.)

## Adding New Public Surface

1. Implement logic in the owning module (`internal_*` or module-local function)
2. Add a thin documented wrapper in `ThirdPartyHooks.lua`
3. Document params, return type, and hook expectations in file header comments

## Existing Integrations — Preserve

Built-in compatibility shims must keep working:
- **TradeJunkie** — reparent open button to `SkilletFrame`
- **ArmorCraft** — reparent craft frame
- **EnchantingSell** — skip Skillet when `ESeller` disables default craft frame

New integration buttons: use `Skillet:AddButtonToTradeskillWindow(button)`.

## Extensibility Points (call, don't hook)

- `AddRecipeSorter(text, method)` — sorting signature: `(tradeskill, indexA, indexB, stitchLeft, stitchRight) -> boolean`
- `AddPreButtonShowCallback` / `AddPreButtonHideCallback`

## Read-Only Query API

`GetCharacters`, `GetCharacterProfessions`, `GetCharacterTradeskills`, `GetCraftersForItem` return cached Stitch data — callers must treat as read-only; do not mutate returned tables.
